<br>
This is not about &quot;boss&quot; encounters really.  Even in that case, it would apply though.  In SoL encounters, you can go totally OOM several times before the boss dies.  In these cases, you don't want to be sitting down to meditate when you could be clicking the robe.<br>
<br>
I am not comparing casting SoS to clicking the robe.  I am comparing casting SoS until OOM to casting SoS once, and clicking robe until mana hits 100% to cast SoS again.<br>
<br>
This is basically an analysis for a constant-pull exp group though, in a zone where you cannot summon your horse/lizard.<br>
<br>
In an exp group, you don't want to go OOM.  You want to do as much sustainable damage over time without any downtime.  This means your maximum damage rate is based on your mana regen rate.  If you exceed that, you eventually end up OOM.<br>
<br>
For anyone who has just recently gotten this robe, the odds are in favor of clicking the robe instead of meditating as long as you have access to KEI and Greater Familiar.  This is ONLY for a situation where you cannot afford any downtime. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xoshia>Xoshia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/03 10:40:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26345.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eviternity.net/Xoshiasdoll.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Foci and click nukes</span><hr size=1> Mixed in with the odd SoS or whatever main nuke your using at the time (mine still draught of ice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), the casts from this robe should leave you with close to a full mana bar which would allow you to do constant damage during groups.<br>
